cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI. 

The paper proposes a new video representation using trajectories, which is a common technique in computer vision applications. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of constraints and similarity measures, which are common in machine learning (cs.MM - Multimedia) and data mining (cs.LG - Machine Learning). The proposed representation can also be used for information retrieval (cs.IR - Information Retrieval) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI - Artificial Intelligence) applications.
